        "timestamp": "2017-04-20 19:47:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nDo you think there is an advantage to making CommandExecutorInput immutable if RuntimeContext is not immutable?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "923f850f1c7efaf235385abf7e86a150cd98e9fc",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 35,
          "name": "Gary Wu",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "gary.wu@gmail.com",
          "username": "gwu"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-04-20 21:18:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe more things are immutable, the easier it is to reason about the code.  It would be great if we can make RuntimeContext immutable as well, but I'm not sure we can do the same exercise all the way down the other objects that it contains.\n\nActually, do we need CommandExecutorInput at all?  It doesn't seem like CommandExecutorInput.getTtl() is ever called.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
